<HEADLINE> NBC's Williams Likes To Race  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   BOZEMAN, Mont. (AP) -- NBC news anchor Brian Williams has a need
for speed.
</P>
<P>
   Williams, 41, drove in an eight-lap stock car race here during
his annual Montana vacation.
</P>
<P>
   Williams said his dad took him to watch stock car races while he
was young, and now he watches races and drives in them whenever he
can.
</P>
<P>
   ''I've tried to do this wherever kind people would let me,''
Williams said. ''The hook's in my mouth.''
</P>
<P>
   On Friday, he was behind the wheel of a rebuilt 1983 Buick Regal
at the Gallatin Speedway. In his first race on a dirt track, he
made the turns without spinning out, but finished last.
</P>
<P>
   Williams left Montana on Saturday for Los Angeles, where he will
help cover the Democratic National Convention.
</P>
