<HEADLINE> 'Mr. Big' Heads to Broadway  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- ''Sex and the City's'' Mr. Big is going to
Broadway. Will a big-time movie career in Hollywood be his next
stop?
</P>
<P>
   Chris Noth isn't sure he wants it to be.
</P>
<P>
   ''I have enough attention already. More, I don't really need,''
said Noth, who plays Mr. Big on the HBO series and was hunk
Detective Mike Logan on ''Law and Order.''
</P>
<P>
   Noth, a Yale School of Drama graduate, dismisses those who
compare him to George Clooney, the last TV star to make the
transition to film stardom.
</P>
<P>
   ''Clooney's got a charm that is really palpable,'' said Noth in
Sunday's editions of the Daily News. ''I'm not sure I have that. No
one is coming to me and offering me a $50 million movie.''
</P>
<P>
   Noth will play Sen. Joe Cantwell in the Broadway revival of Gore
Vidal's ''The Best Man,'' set to open Sept. 17.
</P>
</TEXT>
