<HEADLINE> Jenkins Wins Canada Senior Open  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WINNIPEG, Manitoba (AP) -- Tom Jenkins made a 10-foot birdie putt
on the 18th hole Sunday for a one-shot victory over Kermit Zarley
in the AT&AMP;T Canada Senior Open.
</P>
<P>
   Jenkins's 4-under-par 68 gave him a 14-under 274 total and his
first victory of the year on the Senior PGA Tour.
</P>
<P>
   Zarley's closing 66 at St. Charles Country Club equaled the low
round of the day.
</P>
<P>
   It was Jenkins' second career victory as a senior and the top
prize of $217,500 pushed him over the $1 million mark in official
earnings this year with $1,134,196.
</P>
<P>
   Doug Tewell had a 69 and finished third with a 276, while Bruce
Fleisher, who shared the third-round lead with Jenkins, had a 72
and was another two strokes back.
</P>
<P>
   Hugh Baiocchi was alone at 279 after a final-round 66, while
Leonard Thompson (70), Ed Dougherty (72) and Tom Wargo (68) all
finished at 280.
</P>
<P>
   Jack Nicklaus had a final-round 72 and finished at 283.
</P>
