seven assists, and DeLisha Milton had 11 points.
</P>
<P>
   Jennifer Gillom and Lisa Harrison each scored 16 points for
Phoenix. Tonya Edwards added 12 points and Brandy Reed had 11 for
the Mercury, who dropped the opener 86-71 at home.
</P>
<P>
   The Sparks led 42-36 at halftime, and the Mercury could get no
closer than six points in the second half. A 3-point shot by
Edwards trimmed Los Angeles' lead to 65-57 with 11:45 left, but the
Sparks responded with a 14-2 run to make it 79-59.
</P>
<P>
   The Sparks went on a 10-0 run to take a 27-14 lead. The Mercury
outscored Los Angeles 22-15 during the remainder of the first half
to draw within six points.
</P>
