<HEADLINE> Kings Sign Mathieu Schneider  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   EL SEGUNDO, Calif. (AP) -- Unrestricted free agent defenseman
Mathieu Schneider, who played for the New York Rangers the last two
seasons, signed a contract with the Los Angeles Kings on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   Terms of the deal were not disclosed.
</P>
<P>
   Schneider, 31, had 10 goals and 20 assists in 80 games last
season, and 10 goals and 24 assists in 75 games two years ago.
</P>
<P>
   Previously, he played for Montreal, the New York Islanders and
Toronto. In 708 career games, he has 115 goals and 260 assists.
</P>
<P>
   ''The Kings were at the top of my list right from the start,''
Schneider said. ''I think this is a real good fit for me and my
style of play.''
</P>
<P>
   Kings vice president/general manager Dave Taylor called
Schneider a proven veteran defenseman with great mobility.
</P>
<P>
   ''Mathieu also plays with an edge, has great vision on the ice
and can move the puck,'' Taylor said. ''This move is a significant
upgrade to our defensive corps.''
</P>
