<HEADLINE> Pat Perez Wins Ozarks Open  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SPRINGFIELD, Mo. (AP) -- Pat Perez made a 5-foot birdie putt on
the first hole of a playoff with Mike Heinen and Pat Bates on
Sunday to win the Buy.com Tour's Ozarks Open.
</P>
<P>
   Perez closed with a 3-under-par 69 to match Heinen and Bates at
18-under 270 on the Highland Springs Country Club course. Perez
earned a career-high $76,500 for his first Buy.com title.
</P>
<P>
   ''It feels like I finally accomplished something in my career,''
said Perez, who helped Arizona State to the 1996 NCAA title. ''It's
a real accomplishment to beat these guys.''
</P>
<P>
   Heinen finished with a 66, and Bates shot a 69. Paul Gow (66),
Hugh Royer III (66) and Matt Peterson (68) tied for fourth at 271.
</P>
<P>
   Perez led at 18 under before bogeying the 17th hole, but
scrambled to birdie the par-5 18th to grab the last playoff spot.
</P>
</TEXT>
