<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Long Shot Give Praise Wins Sorrento  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   DEL MAR, Calif. (AP) -- Long shot Give Praise, ridden by Laffit
Pincay Jr., outdueled favorite Fort Lauderdale in the stretch and
went on to a 3&AMP;frac12;-length victory in the $150,000 Sorrento Stakes at
Del Mar on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   Sea Reel finished second, three lengths in front of Fort
Lauderdale in the field of seven 2-year-old fillies
</P>
<P>
   Give Praise, an Ohio-bred daughter of Pioneering, won $90,000
for her second win in three starts. Give Praise paid $18.20, $6.20
and $3 and has career earnings of $107,060.
</P>
<P>
   Give Praise, who carried 116 pounds, covered 6&AMP;frac12; furlongs in 1:17
4-5
</P>
<P>
   Sea Reel returned $3.80 and $2.80, while Fort Lauderdale, the
4-5 favorite, paid $2.40 to show.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
