<HEADLINE> Ome of the World's Oldest Dies  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LAFAYETTE, La. (AP) -- A Louisiana man who lived in three
centuries and was among the oldest people in the world died at the
age of 111.
</P>
<P>
   Edward ''Pops'' Bernard was listed in the Guiness Book of World
Records as one of the oldest living people. He was born on July 22,
1889, drove until he was 96 and raised cattle when he was well into
his 100s, grandson Harold Bernard Jr. said.
</P>
<P>
   Relatives who threw a birthday party in Lafayette for Bernard
last month said he was ready to die. His son said he didn't have
many ailments and wasn't suffering from arthritis or stiffness.
</P>
<P>
   ''I believe it was his choice to leave us,'' Harold Bernard Jr.
said.
</P>
<P>
   Bernard died Friday at his home. He had lived on his own until
about six months ago.
</P>
</TEXT>
